==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Thermotype
<hw>Ther"mo*type</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Thermo-</ets> + <ets>-type</ets>.]</ety> <def>A picture (as
of a slice of wood) obtained by first wetting the object slightly with
hydrochloric or dilute sulphuric acid, then taking an impression with a
press, and next strongly heating this impression.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thermotypy</ent>⟦br⟧
